    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "I found the optimum at **n=10** (30-second windows). With n=2 the model loses\n",
        "most temporal information; with n=30 each window contains only ~10 samples, which\n",
        "is too few for stable mean and std estimates. The performance is relatively flat\n",
        "between n=10 and n=20, so I chose n=10 as it keeps the feature count manageable.\n",
        "\n",
        "## 4.4 Outlier Clipping Threshold\n",
        "\n",
        "I tested different clipping thresholds to assess sensitivity:\n",
        "\n",
        "| Threshold | CV Accuracy |\n",
        "|-----------|-------------|\n",
        "| No clipping | 93.5% |\n",
        "| ±5 | 93.7% |\n",
        "| **±10** | **93.8%** |\n",
        "| ±15 | 93.7% |\n",
        "| ±20 | 93.5% |\n",
        "\n",
        "The result is robust: performance changes by at most 0.3pp across the range. I\n",
        "chose ±10 as the default, which cleanly removes implausible sensor spikes without\n",
        "affecting the bulk of the distribution.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "# Final Model & Kaggle Results\n",
        "\n",
        "## Model Architecture\n",
        "\n",
        "I submitted an **ensemble of gradient boosted trees and a Random Forest** trained\n",
        "on 716 hand-crafted features.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Feature set (716 total):**\n",
        "\n",
        "| Group | Features | Description |\n",
        "|-------|----------|-------------|\n",
        "| mean_x/y/z stats+diff | 78 | 18 stats + 8 trend features per mean channel |\n",
        "| std_x/y/z stats+diff | 78 | Same for each std channel |\n",
        "| acc_mag + std_mag stats+diff | 52 | Vector magnitude channels |\n",
        "| Cross-axis magnitudes stats+diff | 156 | xy_mag, xz_mag, yz_mag and std variants |\n",
        "| Sum features stats+diff | 52 | mean_sum = mean_x+y+z; std_sum |\n",
        "| FFT + peak features | 50 | 5 channels × (6 FFT + 4 peak features) |\n",
        "| 10-window statistics | 250 | 5 channels × 10 segments × 5 stats |\n",
        "\n",
        "**Training setup:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Cross-validation:** I used GroupKFold(5) on user identity — no user appears in\n",
        "  both train and validation within a fold, which mirrors the competition's\n",
        "  train/test structure.\n",
        "- **Classifier:** LightGBM with `num_leaves=31`, `learning_rate=0.01`,\n",
        "  `n_estimators=5000` with early stopping (patience=300).\n",
        "- **Class imbalance:** I used `sample_weight='balanced'` so that C2 (3.2%) and C4\n",
        "  (1.3%) receive proportionally higher weight during training.\n",
        "- **Threshold optimisation:** I applied class-specific probability scaling\n",
        "  (Nelder-Mead optimisation on 8 random restarts) on OOF probabilities to further\n",
        "  boost recall on underrepresented classes.\n",
        "- **Final ensemble:** 5 LightGBM seeds + 2 XGBoost seeds + 1 RandomForest = 8\n",
        "  models, averaged equally.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Performance Progression\n"
      ],
      "id": "7fec38cb"
    },
