        "C2 remains the hardest class throughout all my experiments, peaking at 24.4% F1.\n",
        "I found that 47–52% of its probability mass is consistently assigned to C1 across\n",
        "all model iterations, suggesting the confusion is structural: C1 and C2 share\n",
        "nearly identical std-channel distributions, and only the gravity projection and\n",
        "its temporal drift separate them. Despite extensive feature engineering, I could\n",
        "not push C2 recall above ~24%.\n",
